# Proto Services & Auth

## Services

**Base**: `Common\Services\Service`

Services coordinate business logic; models handle data access. Follow SRP — each method does ONE thing.

### ServiceResult (Standardized Returns)
```php
use Proto\Services\ServiceResult;

public function createGroup(int $userId, int $communityId, array $data): ServiceResult
{
    if (!$this->isGroupSlugUnique($communityId, $data['slug']))
    {
        return ServiceResult::failure('Group slug already exists');
    }
    $group = $this->createGroupRecord($userId, $communityId, $data);
    return $group ? ServiceResult::success($group) : ServiceResult::failure('Failed to create group', 'CREATE_FAILED');
}
```

**API**: `ServiceResult::success($data)`, `ServiceResult::failure($message, $code)`, `$result->success`, `$result->data`, `$result->error`, `$result->code`, `$result->failed()`

**Controller usage**:
```php
$result = $this->service->createGroup($userId, $communityId, $data);
if (!$result->success)
{
    return $this->error($result->error);
}
return $this->response($result->data);
```

### Built-in Service Traits

**ToggleLikeTrait** — like/toggle with atomic counters:
```php
use Proto\Services\Traits\ToggleLikeTrait;

public function togglePostLike(int $userId, int $postId): object
{
    return $this->toggleLike(PostLike::class, Post::class, $userId, $postId, 'postId', 'likeCount');
    // Returns: {liked: bool, likeCount: int}
}
```

**TogglePivotTrait** — generic pivot toggle (bookmarks, favorites, follows):
```php
use Proto\Services\Traits\TogglePivotTrait;

public function toggle(int $userId, string $itemType, int $itemId): object
{
    return $this->togglePivot(Bookmark::class, [
        'userId' => $userId, 'itemType' => $itemType, 'itemId' => $itemId
    ]);
    // Returns: {active: bool, record: ?object}
}
```

**VoteableTrait** — up/down voting with toggle-off, vote-switching, and atomic scores:
```php
use Proto\Services\Traits\VoteableTrait;

public function voteOnPost(int $userId, int $postId, string $direction): object
{
    return $this->vote(ForumPostVote::class, ForumPost::class, $userId, $postId, 'postId', $direction, 'score');
    // Returns: {direction: ?string, score: int}
}
```

**AudienceTargetingTrait** — multi-dimensional targeting:
```php
use Proto\Services\Traits\AudienceTargetingTrait;

protected function getTargetingConfig(): array
{
    return [
        'brands' => ['model' => EventBrandTarget::class, 'fk' => 'eventId'],
        'vehicleTypes' => ['model' => EventVehicleTypeTarget::class, 'fk' => 'eventId'],
        'interests' => ['model' => EventInterestTarget::class, 'fk' => 'eventId', 'valueField' => 'interestId'],
    ];
}
// $service->getTargeting($eventId);
// $service->saveTargets($eventId, $targets);
```

**LocationFilterTrait** — proximity filtering:
```php
use Proto\Services\Traits\LocationFilterTrait;

// Direct filter on POINT column
$this->filterByProximity($filter, [
    'latitude' => $lat, 'longitude' => $lon,
    'radius' => 50, 'alias' => 'v', 'column' => 'position'
]);

// Subquery filter against related table
$this->filterByProximitySubquery($filter, [
    'latitude' => $lat, 'longitude' => $lon,
    'radius' => 50, 'table' => 'user_location_preferences',
    'joinColumn' => 'user_id', 'parentColumn' => 'v.user_id'
]);
```

Methods: `filterByProximity()`, `filterByProximitySubquery()`, `buildProximityCondition()`, `buildProximitySubqueryCondition()`, `convertToMeters()`

### Service Principles & SRP Refactoring

```php
// ❌ WRONG — method doing too much
public function createGroup(int $userId, array $data): object|false
{
    $existing = Group::getBy(['slug' => $data['slug']]);
    if ($existing) return false;
    // ... Stripe setup, group creation, member add, count update all in one method
}

// ✅ CORRECT — delegated to focused methods
public function createGroup(int $userId, int $communityId, array $data): object|false
{
    if (!$this->isGroupSlugUnique($communityId, $data['slug']))
    {
        return false;
    }

    $stripeData = $this->setupGroupStripeIntegration($data);
    if ($stripeData === false) return false;

    $group = $this->createGroupRecord($userId, $communityId, array_merge($data, $stripeData));
    if (!$group) return false;

    $this->addGroupMember($group->id, $userId, 'owner', null);
    $this->incrementCommunityGroupCount($communityId);

    return Group::get($group->id);
}
```

**CRITICAL**:
- Services NEVER instantiate storage classes directly — use model methods
- Always use constructor with object: `new Model((object)[...])`, not verbose property-by-property
- Extract repeated logic into protected helper methods
- Helper methods should be protected unless needed elsewhere
- For complex queries, add static methods to model that delegate to storage

## Validation

**Format**: `'type[:max]|required'`

**Types**: `int`, `float`, `string`, `email`, `ip`, `phone`, `mac`, `bool`, `url`, `domain`

```php
'name' => 'string:255|required',
'email' => 'email|required',
'avatar' => 'image:2048|required|mimes:jpeg,png,gif,bmp,tiff,webp,jxl,heic,heif,avif'
```

**Image validation**: `Proto\Api\ImageValidator::validate($uploadFile, $maxSizeKB, $mimeTypes)`

## Auth & Policies

### Gates
```php
class UserGate extends Gate
{
    public function isUser(int $userId): bool
    {
        $sessionUserId = $this->session->get('user')->id ?? null;
        return $sessionUserId === $userId;
    }

    public function isAdmin(): bool
    {
        return $this->session->get('role') === 'admin';
    }
}

// Register: $auth = auth(); $auth->user = new UserGate();
// Use: auth()->user->isUser(1);
```

### Policies
```php
use Proto\Http\Router\Request;

class UserPolicy extends Policy
{
    protected ?string $type = 'user';

    public function before(Request $request): bool
    {
        return (auth()->user->isAdmin());
    }

    public function default(Request $request): bool
    {
        return false;
    }

    public function get(Request $request): bool
    {
        $id = $this->getResourceId($request);
        $user = User::get($id);
        if (!$user) { return false; }
        return $this->ownsResource($user->id);
    }

    public function afterGet(mixed $result): bool
    {
        $userId = $this->getUserId();
        if (!$userId) return false;
        return ($result->id === $userId);
    }

    public function add(Request $request): bool
    {
        return $this->isSignedIn();
    }

    public function update(Request $request): bool
    {
        return $this->matchesRouteUser($request, 'userId');
    }
}
```

**Built-in Helpers** (on `Common\Auth\Policies\Policy`):
- `$this->isSignedIn()` — checks if user is logged in via session
- `$this->getUserId()` — returns `session()->user->id` or `null`
- `$this->getResourceId(Request $request)` — extracts resource ID
- `$this->ownsResource(mixed $ownerId)` — compares to session user; admins always pass
- `$this->matchesRouteUser(Request $request, string $paramName)` — route param matches session user

### Policy Checklist (CRITICAL)
1. **Always extend `Common\Auth\Policies\Policy`** — NOT `Proto\Auth\Policies\Policy` directly. Common adds `$type`, `ownsResource()`, `hasPermission()`
2. **Always set `protected ?string $type`** — Proto auto-infers from class name if not set (e.g., `EventPolicy` → `'event'`)
3. **Every method MUST accept `(Request $request): bool`** — wrong signature is logged as warning in ALL environments
4. **Use `add()` not `create()`** — framework dispatches POST to `add`
5. **Use built-in helpers** — avoid raw `auth()->user` and manual session checks
6. **Every ResourceController MUST have `protected ?string $policy`** — unprotected controllers are an authorization gap

### Controller Auth Pattern
```php
// ✅ CORRECT - Policy enforces auth, controller uses session directly
class GroupController extends ResourceController
{
    protected ?string $policy = GroupPolicy::class;

    public function join(Request $request): object
    {
        $userId = session()->user->id; // Safe after policy check — no null check needed
        return $this->service->joinGroup($userId, $request->getInt('groupId'));
    }
}
```

### Controller Audit Field Patterns
```php
// Standard modifyAddItem — inject audit fields
protected function modifyAddItem(object &$data, Request $request): void
{
    $data->createdBy = session()->user->id;
}

// Standard modifyUpdateItem (when model has $immutableFields)
// Framework auto-strips immutable fields — just set audit fields
protected function modifyUpdateItem(object &$data, Request $request): void
{
    $data->updatedBy = (int)session()->user->id;
}

// When model does NOT have $immutableFields — manually restrict
protected function modifyUpdateItem(object &$data, Request $request): void
{
    $data->updatedBy = session()->user->id;
    $id = $data->id ?? null;
    $this->restrictFields($data, ['id', 'createdBy', 'createdAt']);
    $data->id = $id;
}
```

**CRITICAL**: Prefer declaring `$immutableFields` on the model over manual `restrictFields()` in controllers.

## File Storage (Vault)

```php
use Proto\Utils\Files\Vault;

// Access uploaded files from request
$uploadFile = $request->file('upload');          // Single file (UploadFile|null)
$attachments = $request->fileArray('attachments'); // Multiple files (UploadFile[])

// Store
$uploadFile->store('local', 'attachments');

// Metadata
$originalName = $uploadFile->getOriginalName();
$newName = $uploadFile->getNewName();
$size = $uploadFile->getSize();
$mimeType = $uploadFile->getMimeType();
if ($uploadFile->isImageFile()) { [$width, $height] = $uploadFile->getDimensions(); }

// Via Vault directly
Vault::disk('local', 'attachments')->add('/tmp/file.txt');
Vault::disk('local', 'attachments')->download('file.txt');
$content = Vault::disk('local')->get('/tmp/file.txt');
Vault::disk('local')->delete('/tmp/file.txt');
Vault::disk('s3', 'uploads')->add('/tmp/file.txt');
```

**CRITICAL**: Use `$request->file('field')` to access uploads, NOT `$_FILES` directly.
